Description: # pymotion [![Build Status](https://travis-ci.com/ludeeus/pymotion.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.com/ludeeus/pymotion) [![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/pymotion.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/pymotion)
        
        _Python API wrapper for Motion webcontrol._
        
        ## Prerequisites
        
        To use this you need to make sure that both these settings has these values:
        You will find these in the `motion.conf` file.
        
        ```
        webcontrol_localhost off
        webcontrol_html_output off
        ```
        
        ## Install
        
        ```bash
        pip install pymotion
        ```
        
        Look at the file `example.py` for a usage example.
